BELGIUM: Highlights of Tuesday's Commission briefing.Highlights of Tuesday's Commission briefing.Following are highlights of the midday briefing by the European Commission on Tuesday:Commission spokesman Nikolaus van der Pas told reporters Competition Commissioner Karel Van Miert would speak by telephone to German Economics Minister Guenter Rexrodt later on Tuesday about the Saxony subsidies case (see BC-STATE AID-VOLKSWAGEN, moving shortly). He said he would brief reporters later on Tuesday about the outcome.- - - -The Commission released the following documents:- IP/96/797: Commission clears Siemens and Sommer Allibert joint venture.- IP/96/798: Commission clears General Electric's CompuNet purchase.- IP/96/799: Commission clears Kloeckner Stahlund Metallhandel buy of 62 percent share in ARUS Distribution Industrielle SA.- IP/96/800: Commission makes 251 million Ecus available to SMEs in Spain.- ME96/20.8: Midday Express.